            <span class="utterance" who="#boderD" start="966.959" end="x">So the general disposition in Poland concerning Jews is what?</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Mira Milgram</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#milgramM" start="972.839" end="x">Hitler has worked there too long. It is a wordless anti-Semitism. The Jews are afraid to be there. And in my opinion the Jews have achieved so much that they deserve to be left in peace. I myself know. [Unintelligible sentence]. I went to school there, I studied at university, I have friends amongst the Polish. But I didn't have a good feeling, I was afraid. I think this will maybe improve after years. But now this is not the place for Jews. The government will do such a thing again, the government does not [unintelligible sentence end].</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#boderD" start="1033.899" end="x">Yes.</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Mira Milgram</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#milgramM" start="1034.683" end="x">But the population, that [unintelligible sentence end].</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">David Boder</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#boderD" start="1041.618" end="x">Mrs. Milgram, and now you want to go to Palestine. And you want . . .</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Mira Milgram</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#milgramM" start="1046.698" end="x">[interrupts] This is my only wish now. I want to bring up my child in Palestine. Because . . .</span>
        </li>
